! $Id: whois_server,v 1.1 2001/12/08 21:44:10 toast Exp $
Usage: FORMAT WHOIS_SERVER <format description>
  Controls how the whois line displaying the server a user is on appears.

  Valid format characters:
       N          Nick of whois target
       S          The whois target's server hostname
       M          The description of the server

  This format has no effect if OLD_WHOIS_FORMAT is ON.

See Also:
  FORMAT WHOIS_ADMIN
  FORMAT WHOIS_AWAY
  FORMAT WHOIS_CHANNELS
  FORMAT WHOIS_IDLE
  FORMAT WHOIS_IRCNAME
  FORMAT WHOIS_NSLOOKUP
  FORMAT WHOIS_OPER
  FORMAT WHOIS_SIGNON
  FORMAT WHOIS_USERHOST
  FORMAT WHOWAS_USERHOST
  SET OLD_WHOIS_FORMAT
  WHOIS
  WHOWAS
